Key Statistics.name: Market Capitalization, $K
Key Statistics.desc: The total equity market value of the company: the shares outstanding times the stock price (in thousands of dollars).

Key Statistics.name: Enterprise Value, $K
Key Statistics.desc: Enterprise Value is the measure of a company’s total value. It is computed by the sum of the current Market Capitalization, Short Term Debt, Long Term Debt, Minority Interests and Preferred Stock minus Cash & Equivalents.

Key Statistics.name: Shares Outstanding, K
Key Statistics.desc: Common shares that have been authorized, issued, and purchased by investors.

Key Statistics.name: 60-Month Beta
Key Statistics.desc: Coefficient that measures the volatility of a stock's returns relative to the market (S&P 500), based on a 60-month historical regression of the return on the stock onto the return on the S&P 500.

Key Statistics.name: % Insider Shareholders
Key Statistics.desc: The percent of ownership held by the company's executives, board of directors, and other senior officials.

Key Statistics.name: % Institutional Shareholders
Key Statistics.desc: The percent of ownership held by large financial institutions or organizations.

Key Statistics.name: Float, K
Key Statistics.desc: The regular shares a company has issued that are available to trade (shares outstanding - restricted stock).

Key Statistics.name: % Float
Key Statistics.desc: The percentage of regular shares a company has issued that are available to trade (float / shares outstanding * 100).

Key Statistics.name: Five-Year Revenue Growth
Key Statistics.desc: The revenue growth percent over a 5-Year period. Growth is based on comparing the value from 5-years ago against the present value, reflected as a percentage.

Key Statistics.name: EBIT(a)
Key Statistics.desc: EBIT, or Earnings before interest and taxes, is a measure of a firm's profit that excludes interest and income tax expenses. Expressed in millions of dollars, EBIT = Revenue - Operating expenses + Non-operating income.

Key Statistics.name: EBITDA(a)
Key Statistics.desc: EBITDA is net income (earnings) with interest, taxes, depreciation, and amortization added back, expressed in millions of dollars.

Earnings.name: Most Recent Earnings
Earnings.desc: Earnings per share, or the portion of a company's profit allocated to each outstanding share of common stock.

Earnings.name: Latest Earnings Date
Earnings.desc: The next reported earnings date, or the latest earnings date as reported by the company (if no future date has been released).

Earnings.name: Report Released
Earnings.desc: The date on which the earnings report is released.

Earnings.name: Earnings Per Share ttm
Earnings.desc: Earnings per share, or the portion of a company's profit allocated to each outstanding share of common stock, for the last trailing twelve months.

Earnings.name: EPS Growth vs. Prev Quarter
Earnings.desc: The earnings per share growth over the previous quarter.

Earnings.name: EPS Growth vs. Prev Year
Earnings.desc: The earnings per share growth from the most recent EPS compared to the quarterly EPS from 4 quarters before.

Earnings.name: 5-Year Earnings Growth
Earnings.desc: The earnings growth percent over a 5-Year period.

Dividends & Splits.name: Dividend Rate
Dividends & Splits.desc: The trailing annual dividend amount paid.

Dividends & Splits.name: Dividend Yield
Dividends & Splits.desc: Annual dividend yield is trailing annual dividend amount divided by the latest closing price.

Dividends & Splits.name: Last Dividend Date
Dividends & Splits.desc: The ex-dividend date on which the most recent dividend was paid.

Dividends & Splits.name: Dividend Date
Dividends & Splits.desc: The next ex-dividend date, or the latest ex-dividend date if no future date has been released.

Dividends & Splits.name: Dividend Payable Date
Dividends & Splits.desc: The next dividend payable date, or the latest dividend payable date if no future date has been released.

Dividends & Splits.name: Dividend Payout Ratio
Dividends & Splits.desc: Dividend payout ratio is the % of net income paid to stockholders in dividends.

Dividends & Splits.name: 5-Year Dividends Growth
Dividends & Splits.desc: The dividends growth percent over a 5-Year period.

Dividends & Splits.name: Split
Dividends & Splits.desc: The share split recorded on the last split date.

Dividends & Splits.name: Split Date
Dividends & Splits.desc: The date on which a share split last occurred.

Financial Ratios.name: Price/Earnings ttm
Financial Ratios.desc: The closing price divided by the earnings-per-share based on the last trailing twelve months (TTM) of earnings.

Financial Ratios.name: Price/Earnings Forward
Financial Ratios.desc: The projected price to earnings per share valuation.

Financial Ratios.name: Return-on-Equity %
Financial Ratios.desc: For the recent quarter (after taxes): earnings from total operations (not including extraordinary items) divided by the Most Recent Quarter Common Stock Equity.

Financial Ratios.name: Return-on-Assets %
Financial Ratios.desc: For the recent quarter (before taxes): earnings from total operations (not including extraordinary items) divided by the Most Recent Quarter Assets.

Financial Ratios.name: Profit Margin %
Financial Ratios.desc: For the recent year, a measure of profitability, equal to annual net income / revenues over the selected period * 100.

Financial Ratios.name: Debt/Equity
Financial Ratios.desc: The debt/equity ratio for the latest quarter. Debt/Equity is a financial health ratio that adds long-term debt to current liabilities, then divides by the last fiscal year net equity per share of common stock.

Financial Ratios.name: Price/Sales
Financial Ratios.desc: Latest closing price of the stock divided by the last twelve months revenue/sales per share.

Financial Ratios.name: Price/Cash Flow
Financial Ratios.desc: Latest closing price of the stock divided by the last twelve months revenue/cash flow per share.

Financial Ratios.name: Price/Book
Financial Ratios.desc: A financial ratio used to compare a company's current market price to its book value.

Financial Ratios.name: Book Value/Share
Financial Ratios.desc: The per share value of a company based on its equity available to common shareholders for the trailing 12 months.

Financial Ratios.name: Interest Coverage
Financial Ratios.desc: A measure of a company's ability to honor its interest payments.  (Annual Pre-Tax Income + Annual Interest Expense) / Annual Interest Expense

Analysts & Estimates.name: Analyst Rating
Analysts & Estimates.desc: The current average Analyst Rating, where Strong Buy = 5, Moderate Buy = 4, Hold = 3, Moderate Sell = 2, Strong Sell = 1.

ETFs Data Fields.name: Assets Under Management
ETFs Data Fields.desc: Assets Under Management (AUM) is the total market value of all financial assets managed by the ETF or Fund.

ETFs Data Fields.name: Net Asset Value
ETFs Data Fields.desc: Net Asset Value (NAV) is the per share price of the fund (total net assets / number of shares outstanding, minus fees & expenses.)

ETFs Data Fields.name: Management Fee
ETFs Data Fields.desc: An expense ratio that measures what it costs the investment company to manage the ETF.

ETFs Data Fields.name: Alpha
ETFs Data Fields.desc: A measurement of how an ETF is performing in relation to its benchmark index.

Futures Data Fields.name: Contract Name
Futures Data Fields.desc: A shortened version of the symbol name.

Futures Data Fields.name: Expiration Date
Futures Data Fields.desc: The expiration date for a futures contract.

Futures Data Fields.name: Days Till Expiration
Futures Data Fields.desc: The number of days until the futures contract expires.

Futures Data Fields.name: First Notice Date
Futures Data Fields.desc: The first notice date for a futures contract, after which time the owner of the contract can take physical delivery of the underlying asset.

Futures Data Fields.name: Days Till First Notice
Futures Data Fields.desc: The number of days until the futures contract first notice, after which time the owner of the contract can take physical delivery of the underlying asset

Futures Data Fields.name: Point Value
Futures Data Fields.desc: A measure of one basis point change in the futures price

Futures Data Fields.name: Margin
Futures Data Fields.desc: The approximate amount of money that you must deposit and keep on hand with your broker when you open a futures position.

Futures Data Fields.name: Open Interest
Futures Data Fields.desc: The total number of open contracts for the previous day that have been traded but not yet liquidated via offsetting trades.

Portfolio Data Fields.desc: The quantity open on the transaction.
Portfolio Data Fields.name: Quantity

Portfolio Data Fields.desc: Initial transaction position, either Buy or Sell.
Portfolio Data Fields.name: Action

Portfolio Data Fields.desc: The price at which the initial transaction was entered at.
Portfolio Data Fields.name: Entry Price

Portfolio Data Fields.desc: The date on which the transaction was closed.
Portfolio Data Fields.name: Exit Date

Portfolio Data Fields.desc: The price at which the transaction was closed.
Portfolio Data Fields.name: Exit Price

Portfolio Data Fields.desc: The total fees associated with the transaction.
Portfolio Data Fields.name: Commission

Portfolio Data Fields.desc: The current market value (Last Price if no Exit Price, or Entry Price for a Sell transaction) * Quantity.
Portfolio Data Fields.name: Stock Value

Portfolio Data Fields.desc: The daily profit or loss. This field is blank if trade is liquidated before today.
Portfolio Data Fields.name: Daily Return

Portfolio Data Fields.desc: The total dollar change (the difference between the Exit Price (or Last Price, if no Exit Price) and the Entry Price).
Portfolio Data Fields.name: Total Price Change

Investor Portfolio Data Fields.name: Quantity
Investor Portfolio Data Fields.desc: The quantity open for the asset.

Investor Portfolio Data Fields.name: Market Value
Investor Portfolio Data Fields.desc: The current market value for the investment (last price x open quantity)

Investor Portfolio Data Fields.name: Cost Basis
Investor Portfolio Data Fields.desc: Cost Basis is the price paid to purchase the open positions, including reinvested dividends or capital gains distributions, and fees.

Investor Portfolio Data Fields.name: Average Cost
Investor Portfolio Data Fields.desc: The average cost to purchase the asset, including reinvestment of dividends or capital gains distributions, and fees.

Investor Portfolio Data Fields.name: % of Portfolio
Investor Portfolio Data Fields.desc: The percent an asset represents of the overall Portfolio market value.

Investor Portfolio Data Fields.name: Realized Gain
Investor Portfolio Data Fields.desc: The total profit or loss that has resulted from selling the asset.

Investor Portfolio Data Fields.name: Today's Gain
Investor Portfolio Data Fields.desc: For the current trading day, the theoretical profit (or loss).

Investor Portfolio Data Fields.name: Gain Since Inception
Investor Portfolio Data Fields.desc: The total gain/loss for the investment since inception of the portfolio.

Investor Portfolio Data Fields.name: % Since Inception
Investor Portfolio Data Fields.desc: The total percent gain/loss for the investment since inception of the portfolio.

Investor Portfolio Data Fields.name: Gain/Loss
Investor Portfolio Data Fields.desc: The total gain/loss for the investment for the current year

Investor Portfolio Data Fields.name: % Gain/Loss
Investor Portfolio Data Fields.desc: The total gain/loss percent for the investment for the current year

Investor Portfolio Data Fields.name: Prior Gain/Loss
Investor Portfolio Data Fields.desc: The total gain/loss for the investment for the previous year

Investor Portfolio Data Fields.name: Prior % Gain/Loss
Investor Portfolio Data Fields.desc: The total gain/loss percent for the investment for the previous year

Investor Portfolio Data Fields.name: Gain/Loss 2 yrs ago
Investor Portfolio Data Fields.desc: The total gain/loss for the investment 2 years ago

Investor Portfolio Data Fields.name: % Gain/Loss 2 yrs ago
Investor Portfolio Data Fields.desc: The total gain/loss percent for the investment 2 years ago
